column14: Measured 50m u/s of bridge 2.5km d/s of station. No overflow. @ Uncertainty: IVE method 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ On arrival ice surface is wet and has been recently flooded. Thin ice layer on top of 0.05m overflow water over >1m thick ice. First DWL (13:30) taken in overflow at shore. Then drilled a hole near shore found ice to shore/bed. Water appeared to be draining down hole left station to measure Q downstream thinking it may equalize with main channel. Water level did not appear to have changed much ~2hrs later probably not equalizing. Drilled another hole farther towards mid-channel to try to connect to main channel. Drilled down 1.2m (extended flighting length) not able to drill through ice completely. Water was draining down hole surface ice cracking as water was moving. Surveyed again (16:05) still unsure if surface water measured is connected to main channel (i.e. representative of what sensors are reading) and even if so it could take hours to equalize. DWL consistent over last 30mins of visit but still cannot be relied upon as it could be isolated overflow. No reset. Will need to wait to apply SRC based on next open water visit. MGH found from logger values before and after measurement no SRC applied- SRC will be required when found on next open water visit. Mid-section
